\/tr><\/table><div class = \"text-block\"><ol style = \"list-style-type: decimal;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Incubate for 30 min at 70\u00b0C<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Ideally and if DNA conc. is high engouh\n(> 50ng\/\u00b5l), do another quick cleanup with the Promega Kit.<\/li><\/ol><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"15A5DDBC8FDA4D1FB0E0C224C7D98119","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<table border><tr style = \"text-align:center;\"><td>  <\/td><td>A<\/td><td>B<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">1<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">PCR Product<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">1-7\u00b5l<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">2<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">10x Taq Buffer<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">1\u00b5l<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">3<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">ATP to 0.2mM<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">1\u00b5l<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">4<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">Taq DNA Pol 5U<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">1\u00b5l<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">5<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">dH<sub>2<\/sub>O<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">to 10\u00b5l<\/td><\/tr><\/table>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":464273,"guid":"B45B1A951EA54CCB892FB0CB682D7BF4","previous_id":464170,"previous_guid":"DE21916A4B194D08B3D3F5CB6D7DE81B","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"4EB5379F88BD41C9954F59D6D2A1B54A","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Ligation  (Day 1)"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"52F65E8E23E64EC2AF0EABA0CE0A9AD4","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Calculate the ratio of Vector:Insert (use molar ratios of 1:1 or 3:1):<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/jfsfzyn.png\" \/><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Mix the following reagents:<\/div><table border><tr style = \"text-align:center;\"><td>  <\/td><td>A<\/td><td>B<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">1<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">Vector (50ng\/\u00b5l) 3kb<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">50ng<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">2<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">Insert<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">xng<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">3<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">2x Rapid Lig. Buff.<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">1\u00b5l<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">4<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">T4 Ligase<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">1\u00b5l<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">5<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">dH<sub>2<\/sub>O<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">to 10\u00b5l<\/td><\/tr><\/table><div class = \"text-block\">Incubate at 4\u00b0C over night for maximum ligation efficiency or 3 hours at room temperature.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"68DD38334BE944988FE57C15FA11ED8A","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<table border><tr style = \"text-align:center;\"><td>  <\/td><td>A<\/td><td>B<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">1<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">Vector (50ng\/\u00b5l) 3kb<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">50ng<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">2<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">Insert<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">xng<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">3<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">2x Rapid Lig. Buff.<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">1\u00b5l<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">4<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">T4 Ligase<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">1\u00b5l<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">5<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">dH<sub>2<\/sub>O<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">to 10\u00b5l<\/td><\/tr><\/table>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":464385,"guid":"46F0ABEF340E4C82B755415FE3218CC1","previous_id":464273,"previous_guid":"B45B1A951EA54CCB892FB0CB682D7BF4","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"88D933E620904F8CA82BB5204638DBFA","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Transformation (Day 2)"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"06422F3329914862A9A607B2051AA18E","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><ol style = \"list-style-type: decimal;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\"><span>Thaw DH5\u237a<\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\"> on ice\u00a0<\/span><span>(100 \u00b5l in tube)<\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\"><span>Add 3\u00b5l of ligation to 50\u00b5l of cells, mix by stirring gently with tip\u00a0& incubate <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">on ice<\/span><span> for 20 min<\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Heat shock in water bath at 42\u00b0C for 30\u00a0sec<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\"><span>Return tubes <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">to ice<\/span><span> for 2 min<\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Add 53\u00b5l of transformed cells to 250\u00b5l of LB and incubate at 37\u00b0C for 60 min<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Melt LB agar\u00a0in microwave and keep at 50\u00b0C in water bath<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Prepare 50ml of LB+Agar (2 plates): Add 37.5\u00b5l Carbencillin (Stock: 100mg\/ml Plate:75\u00b5g\/ml), 50\u00b5l of X-Gal \/IPTG (Stock: 2%\/0.1M Plate: 1:1000)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Plate 150\u00b5l of LB+cells onto 1 plate and incubate at 37\u00b0C over night<\/li><\/ol><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":464564,"guid":"41D35589F2B94018A2E1E5DF5B6A8B18","previous_id":464385,"previous_guid":"46F0ABEF340E4C82B755415FE3218CC1","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"C5386CA6FE1A46759A07C13976115628","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Identify colonies (Day 3)"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"31076B92102840C59D21436A651D6331","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><ol style = \"list-style-type: decimal;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Remove plates from 37\u00b0C the next morning and check for colonies<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Keep in the fridge for a couple of hours or until next morning so blue\/white colours become more\u00a0intense<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Prepare master mix using a primer in the insert and the M13 fwd\/rev primers to verify insert.\u00a0(Can use blue colonies and M13 primers as neg. control)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Prepare 50ml of LB+Agar (2 plates): Add 37.5\u00b5l Carbencillin (Stock: 100mg\/ml Plate:75\u00b5g\/ml), 50\u00b5l of X-Gal \/IPTG\u00a0(Stock: 2%\/0.1M Plate: \u00a01:1000) and pick verified colonies as stock<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Grow verified colonies over night in LB + Carbencillin (5ml LB + 5\u00b5l Cabencillin (100mg\/ml dilutes to 100\u00b5g\/ml))<\/li><\/ol><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":464682,"guid":"C3A2B368017C48EFBF7DD714FC7B61E4","previous_id":464564,"previous_guid":"41D35589F2B94018A2E1E5DF5B6A8B18","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"1F7F21A3CF4D4CC78DDA06B6FB7DC36D","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Wizard Plus Promega Mini Prep Kit (Day 4)"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"D04281DCD2744142872FB5D1E2AD5E84","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Prepare a glycerol stock:<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ol style = \"list-style-type: decimal;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Mix 150\u00b5l cells with 150\u00b5l glycerol<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\"><span>Store at -80\u00b0C\n\n<\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Production of clear lysate:<\/span><span>\n\n<\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Pellet 5ml of overnight culture for 5 minutes at 4000rpm.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Thoroughly resuspend pellet with 250\u00b5l of Cell Resuspension Solution.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Add 250\u00b5l of Cell Lysis Solution to each sample and leave until it clears up; invert 4 times to mix.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Add 10\u00b5l of Alkaline Protease Solution; invert 4 times to mix. Incubate 5 minutes at room temperature.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Add 350\u00b5l of Neutralization Solution; invert 4 times to mix.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\"><span>Centrifuge at top speed for 10 minutes at room temperature.\n\n<\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Binding of Plasmid DNA:<\/span><span>\n\n<\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Insert Spin Column into Collection Tube.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Decant cleared lysate into Spin Column.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\"><span>Centrifuge at top speed for 1 minute at room temperature. Discard flowthrough, and reinsert Column into Collection Tube.\n\n<\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Washing:<\/span><span>\n\n<\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\"><span>Add 750\u00b5l of Wash Solution (<\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">ethanol added<\/span><span>). Centrifuge at top speed for 1 minute. Discard flowthrough and reinsert column into Collection\u00a0Tube.<\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Repeat Step 1. with 250\u00b5l of Wash Solution.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\"><span>Centrifuge at top speed for 2 minutes at room temperature.\n\n<\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Elution:<\/span><span>\n\n<\/span><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Transfer Spin Column to a sterile 1.5ml microcentrifuge tube, being careful not to transfer any of the Column Wash Solution with the Spin Column. If the Spin Column has Column Wash Solution associated with it, centrifuge again for 1 minute at top speed, then transfer the Spin Column to a new, sterile 1.5ml microcentrifuge tube.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Add 100\u00b5l of Nuclease-Free Water to the Spin Column. Centrifuge at top speed for 1 minute at room temperature.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Discard column, and store DNA at \u201320\u00b0C or below.<\/li><\/ol><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":464761,"guid":"A7DA3974CF0B46928340F5A83E64D0C5","previous_id":464682,"previous_guid":"C3A2B368017C48EFBF7DD714FC7B61E4","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"71275EA0D68A4C458CFB8C244AB8E11A","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Send to sequencing (Day 4)"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"239174ADBDC446DE9C5C1F7DF3A7BE0E","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><ol style = \"list-style-type: decimal;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Measure DNA concentration on plate reader and check 260\/280 & 260\/230 values<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Dilute samples to\u00a0100ng\/\u00b5l<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Prepare a 1:3 dilution (to 3.2pmol\/\u00b5l) of sequencing primers<\/li><\/ol><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":null,"materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><\/div>","changed_on":1569329064}